##Discharge from hospital for more than 2 hours, she "Fu Yang" 

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Intern, Liu Yuxiu, _ paper _ journalist, Zhu Ying

February 17, is the day Xu Jia (not her real name) was discharged from hospital, is also the day she was admitted to hospital.

That afternoon, after two consecutive negative tests for the new coronavirus nucleic acid, she was discharged from the Living Room Shelter Hospital in Wuhan. Back home, after a hot pot of mother's lamb, a bath, and before she could get a good night's sleep, the phone rang -- as if her third nucleic acid test, done the day before she was released from the hospital, came back positive.

So, more than 2 hours after discharge, she returned to the Shelter Hospital.

As of 10:00 on March 10, a total of 80,924 people were confirmed to have contracted NCP, of which 59,982 had been cured and discharged. Since February, there are many patients discharged from hospital nucleic acid test reexamination was positive phenomenon (hereinafter referred to as "Fu Yang") .

In Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province, residents greeted the two patients with flowers after they were discharged from the hospital. Two days later, they were found to have tested positive for nucleic acid. They were readmitted to the hospital and the community was closed. In Tianjin, a patient was retested positive 16 days after discharge, was readmitted, both times turned negative, and was discharged 3 days later. In Guangdong Province, 14% of the discharged patients presented as "Fuyang Foshan" , deputy director of the Guangdong Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Song Tie, announced the figure at a press conference on February 25.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mr Wong, a new-crown pneumonia patient in Xuzhou, was welcomed home by residents of his neighbourhood when he was released from quarantine on February 24. Two days later, he tested positive for nucleic acid. Video capture

Doctors at several designated hospitals in Wuhan told The Paper news that a large number of "Fu Yang" patients were in fact "false negative" caused by nucleic acid testing errors. In addition, the virus in the patients' bodies was not completely eliminated, and their immunity dropped after discharge from the hospital, may Lead to "Fu Yang" .

Several experts also said that some patients have always been unable to produce antibodies, leading to multiple "Fu Yang. ". The "new crown" does not rule out the possibility of chronic carrier, so that it will become less pathogenic.

The seventh edition of the new coronary pneumonia protocol, released in early March, includes antibody testing for both confirmed and suspected cases. A number of front-line doctors suggested including it in the discharge criteria to reduce the "Fu Yang. ". Some doctors also suggested that the standard discharge of lung imaging indicators to quantify, further reduce misjudgment.

"surveillance showed that there was no recurrence of transmission of the disease to other patients in Fuyang, " Guo Yanhong, an inspector of the Medical Administration and Hospital Authority under the National Health Commission, said on February 28, there's a lot to learn.

"Fu Yang" puzzle

Xujia still can't figure out how the virus got to her.

The discomfort was on January 22nd. She was tired, cough, and then began to fever, to Wuhan Tianyou Hospital for a CT, showed a little infection in the right lower lung, the doctor prescribed her home quarantine. After 4 days reexamination, the condition became more serious, became double lung infection, some showed ground glass-like changes. She began lining up at the hospital for fluids and nucleic acid tests.

On February 7, she was admitted to the Living Room Shelter Hospital in Wuhan after testing positive for nucleic acid.

In the Shelter Hospital, Xu Jia watched her patients change from sickly to optimistic, in better and better spirits. Some people follow the popular drama, others follow the nurses to dance in the square, we encourage each other, cheer, let her feel warm.

After being hospitalized, Xu Jia did two nucleic acid tests, both negative. On February 16th for the third time. That day, the attending physician and her video interview, said she two nucleic acid negative, clear absorption of lung inflammation, coupled with a few days without fever, in line with the fifth version of the diagnosis and treatment program discharge criteria. She was pleasantly surprised.

On Feb. 17, Xu said goodbye to her patients and nurses, and posted a photo of her with a nurse on her friend's facebook page. In the photo, she had a bright smile.

Unexpectedly, more than 2 hours after discharge from the hospital, she was told that the third nucleic acid is positive, to the hospital immediately. The nurse saw her return and said, "I don't know whether to welcome you or not... "

She had a sleepless night. The next day she had her fourth nucleic acid test, praying that her last positive result was an accident, but she was soon disappointed. And the family home quarantine, only two days to the end of observation, because her short-term discharge, were sent to the school re-isolation 14 days.

Xu Jia himself began to feel unwell, dizziness, fatigue, high fever, a few days later transferred to the gold and Silver Lake Hospital. Fortunately, after the infusion, the disease was under control.

On March 5, Xu Jia was discharged for the second time. This time, instead of going home, she was sent to a school under lock and key -- an addition to the National Institutes of Health's new pneumonia diagnosis and treatment protocol (Trial Version 7) , released on March 4.

The sixth edition of the treatment plan released on February 19 was first proposed. After discharge, patients were advised to undergo 14-day "self-health monitoring" and return to the hospital for follow-up in the second and fourth weeks, the seventh edition was enhanced to 14 days of "quarantine management and Health Monitoring" .

This change is due to the phenomenon of Fuyang appearing in many places in China.

Experts interviewed believe that the so-called "Fu Yang" in a considerable part of the population is "false negative" , the patient's body has not cleared the virus, only the nucleic acid test did not detect before discharge.

Tong Chaohui, a member of the Expert Group of the Central Committee's Steering Group to Hubei, also said in an interview with CCTV that Fuyang is related to the instability of nucleic acid testing, there are problems with reagent kits, and there are also problems with sampling. The national proportion of Fuyang is about 0.1 percent, it's under control.

In addition, "Fu Yang" may also be detected in the body virus fragments or dead virus, "this does not mean the patient has not been cured or the condition of repeated illness, " Wuhan Tongji Hospital, Deputy Director of the Department of infection, Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou told The Paper news, at present, few patients with Fuyang have symptoms, "relapse" is a very small number.

Peng Zhiyong, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, found that one of the common characteristics of patients with Fuyang was that their lungs improved and were basically normal when they left the hospital, but their immune system did not fully recover after being damaged by the virus, the amount of lymphocyte, absolute value etc. is 20%-30% lower than normal level, cause virus"rise again".

Xu Haibo, director of the Imaging Department of the hospital, also believes that Fu Yang is related to the patient's immunity. Zhang Xiaochun, deputy director of the imaging department, added to thepaper.cn that decreased immunity is prone to relapse and the amount of virus in the body increases again, but the pathological mechanism of the phenomenon has yet to be demonstrated.

Tracing back to "false negative"

NUCLEIC ACID testing has been regarded as the main criteria for the diagnosis and discharge of NCP. The sampling methods included throat swabs, anal swabs, sputum and Bronchoalveolar lavage fluid. The most commonly used are throat swabs, including NASOPHARYNGEAL SWABS and oropharyngeal swabs.

Throat swab is a swab to the throat of patients to extract secretions, collection process, patients prone to cough, vomiting reaction, collection is more difficult.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhong Nanshan team and the Shenyang Institute of Automation Team in the ward to carry out robot experiments. On March 8, the team performed the first robotic throat swab test on a positive patient.

NASOPHARYNGEAL swabs need to be deep in the nasal cavity, less human interference, can obtain a more adequate sample, but patients will not be comfortable, or even nasal bleeding.

According to Li Yan, director of the Laboratory Department at Wuhan University People's Hospital, the new coronavirus mainly resides in the lower respiratory tract, such as the lungs, trachea and Bronchi, while the NASOPHARYNX and Oropharynx reside in the upper respiratory tract. In the early stage, there are some viruses in the respiratory tract, less in the late stage, and there may be virus residue in the NASOPHARYNX, but it may not be collected.

According to clinical observations, the positive rate of NASOPHARYNGEAL SWABS is slightly higher than that of Oropharyngeal Swabs, so his hospital prefers to take nasopharyngeal swabs, but also takes patients'needs into account, Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou, deputy director of the Department of Infection at Wuhan Tongji Hospital, told The Paper.

Many clinicians introduced that the number of patients with viral load, virus distribution, kit quality, sampling methods, sample quality, testing, technical staff level, etc. , will affect the results of nucleic acid testing.

Wang Chen, president of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences, said in an interview with CCTV on February 5 that the positive rate of nucleic acid testing was only 30%-50% .

Of the 44 patients who were found to be twice nucleic acid negative, 26 were declared as positive for the third time —— A discovery made by Zhang Zhanzhan, a physician in the Department of respiratory and Critical Care Medicine at Wuhan University People's Hospital. According to Zhang, this could be a false negative result of a test kit problem, or a patient's viral load dropping during recovery, resulting in intermittent detox, which could result in intermittent negative detox and positive detox. To that end, she recommends three consecutive negative nucleic acid discharge.

Wang Wei (not his real name) , a neurologist at a designated hospital in Wuhan, found it easy to get a false negative when swabs were taken from just one place. He met a patient, checked his throat 12 times, all negative, checked his urine 13 times, came back positive.

In order to improve the diagnostic accuracy, the sixth edition of the diagnostic protocol, nucleic acid test added "sputum, Nasopharyngeal Swab, " and other respiratory specimens, it is recommended to retain sputum as far as possible. In the seventh edition of the diagnostic protocol, emphasis is placed on nucleic acid testing and lower respiratory specimens (sputum or airway aspirates) are more accurate.

Wang Wei told The Paper news that his hospital had "done a lot of oropharynx in the early days, and now Oropharynx, urine and sputum have to be done. ".

It is understood that some hospitals also through continuous multiple sampling, anal swab (stool) , the use of different batches of kits and other ways to improve the accuracy of nucleic acid testing.

NUCLEIC ACID testing requires a basic amount of the virus to be detected, which is higher in the Lower Airways than in the upper airways, so sampling from the Upper Airways can be false negative no matter how many times it is tested, Zhang explained. In addition, some patients with high respiratory viral load, some patients with high viral load in the digestive tract, different sampling site, nucleic acid test results may also be different.

On the basis of national treatment plans, Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou suggested that each region should be flexible in responding to its own medical resources and patients'conditions. In some areas with a high recovery rate, in addition to the two throat swabs, an additional anal swab test can be added and three times negative before discharge.

Controversy over discharge criteria

Besides nucleic acid testing, lung imaging is another important indicator of discharge. Prior to discharge from hospital, the patient's pulmonary inflammation was "significantly absorbed" as required by the previous criteria -- "significant improvement in acute exudative disease" as required by the 6th and 7th Editions.

"obviously absorbed, meaning absorbed to what extent? " A radiologist at Wuhan University People's Hospital told The Paper that different people have different abilities to absorb lung inflammation, and some take a long time. Without objective criteria and quantitative indicators, the diagnosis depends primarily on the experience of the doctor.

Wang Wei revealed that his hospital bed in February, in order to speed up turnover, improve capacity, patients as long as the discharge criteria, were discharged.

"If you don't discharge him, who will help the other patients? There are many tradeoffs to be made, " one doctor interviewed told thepaper.cn. There are many early patients, and "significant absorption" and "significant improvement" in the criteria for diagnosis and treatment give doctors some flexibility.

But Wang Wei found that some of the patients at his hospital were still struggling to breathe oxygen and walk, some had obvious symptoms that required treatment, and some had lungs that he didn't see improving significantly. "discharge criteria are too broad, " he said.

As a result, some discharged patients'clinical symptoms are worse than those of newly admitted patients with mild illness. If their nucleic acid test is "false negative" before discharge, the risk of "Fu Yang" is high.

Wang Wei had seen patients discharged from other designated hospitals and was readmitted because "they were not well enough to be released" after being discharged from the hospital with worsening symptoms.

By late February, however, the number of patients had dwindled, and the hospital began to extend the stay of some patients.

Another doctor interviewed said that his hospital would now allow some patients with hormone use, older, slow recovery from the hospital later discharge, more observation period, to avoid the hospital after "Yang. ".

Zhang Xiaochun told reporters that the standards implemented by the hospital are more detailed than those in the national diagnosis and treatment plan. She is in the south-central Hospital for example, now require patients with acute inflammation complete absorption, 5 consecutive negative nucleic acid can be discharged.

To make it easier for frontline doctors to measure and judge lung conditions, Guangdong Province has quantified the "apparent absorption" of inflammation in the lungs as a minimum recovery of 50 percent, southern weekend reported.

However, Zhang Xiaochun believes that the image is not easy to quantify, each person's constitution is different, some lung disease recovery 50% , no problem, some recovery 90% may also be repeated, need to combine other indicators comprehensive judgment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Xiaochun, people's Daily client chart

Add "antibody test"

Antibody testing was introduced for the first time in the seventh edition of the diagnostic and therapeutic standards, released on March 4.

The new diagnostic criteria included: IGM antibody and IgG antibody were positive, IgG antibody changed from negative to positive or increased 4 times or more in convalescence than in acute stage. The new coronavirus nucleic acid test was negative for two consecutive times (at least 24 hours between samples) , and the IGM and IgG antibodies were still negative 7 days after onset.

IGM and IGG antibodies are normally produced in the body after infection. IGM antibody is the earliest antibody after human infection, usually 3-5 days after infection, suggesting a new infection, can be used for early diagnosis of infection, the disease disappeared soon after recovery.

Igg antibody is a protective antibody, 2 weeks after infection with the virus began to produce, a longer period of time, there may be lifelong carrier, that has been infected with the virus. The higher the IgG level, the more antibodies, the stronger the resistance to the virus.

Antibody detection can determine whether there is a new coronavirus antibody in the body. Both IGM and IGG antibodies were negative, indicating no infection or infection without producing antibodies, and both were positive, indicating recent infection and presence of the virus in the body, Li Yan, director of the laboratory of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, told thepaper.cn IGM is negative, IgG is positive, indicating that patients in the recovery period, has produced antibodies, is the safest.

Li Yan said his hospital started as an antibody test volunteer for infected doctors, taking blood every three days to observe the pattern of antibody tests, which doctors were willing to participate in. The assessment results are also good and are now being used in the screening of incoming patients.

Compared with nucleic acid detection, antibody detection is easy to sample, only need to draw blood, more than ten minutes results; moreover, as long as there is a virus in the blood, it can be detected, less interference by other factors, can make up for the lack of nucleic acid detection, it is helpful for the evaluation and diagnosis of the patient's immunity.

Some hospitals are also beginning to use antibody tests on discharged patients to avoid false negative nucleic acid.

On March 3, the Jiangan Shelter Hospital in Wuhan was informed by the Municipal Epidemic Prevention Headquarters that in order to reduce the recurrence of the disease and achieve the goal of "zero return" , all patients who are to be discharged from the hospital will be given blood samples and tested for antibodies against the virus to ensure their full recovery.

Li Yan explained that the IGG was four times higher than the IGM, indicating that the patient had developed strong antibodies and recovered well, plus two negative nucleic acids, "and [ discharged ] with no problems at all. "

After testing some of the Fu Yang patients for antibodies, Li Yan found that they basically have antibodies, but the number is not high, relatively weak immunity.

"By now, in the middle or late stages of the epidemic, patients who have had a latent infection should have developed antibodies, so you can screen all new patients for antibodies and screen them, " Li Yan said.

Zhang Xiaochun also suggested that if the sensitivity of antibody testing reaches the sensitivity of nucleic acid testing, antibody testing can be included in the discharge criteria, but it can not be required to meet the criteria of antibody testing positive, because a small number of patients may not be able to produce antibodies.

She believes that, with antibody testing, patients can be discharged if they meet four of the five criteria for discharge.

However, at present, antibody detection technology is not yet mature, the kit has just been developed, there is room for improvement. Moreover, the timing and amount of antibody production varies from person to person, making it difficult to provide definitive answers in a treatment plan.

The possibility of a chronic carrier

Is it possible that "Fu Yang" is secondary infection after discharge from hospital?

In an interview with Caijing, the School of Biomedical Sciences at the Li Ka Shing Faculty of Medicine said that it is against the basic principles of virology and immunology for a recovered person to get infected again immediately. The human body relies on the immune response against the virus, the immune response after the encounter of the virus will be activated, not in a short period of time quickly subsided. No more infections for at least six months, a year.

"based on the experience of SARS, the vast majority of people can produce antibodies that can last for a period of time, but it can not be ruled out that some people do not produce antibodies when they leave the hospital, and their illness will return after they leave the hospital, " Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou told thepaper.cn.

Personal Age, Diet, sleep, physical conditions and so on can affect immunity, and then affect the production of antibodies. Doctors often advise patients to eat eggs, drink milk, supplement vitamins, high-quality protein, improve immunity.

But Li Yan found that some patients had made a good clinical recovery, testing positive for all five nucleic acids but producing no antibodies.

One of her colleagues, who is in her 50s, and his wife have been infected for a month, tested positive for nucleic acid, had no clinical symptoms, had few shadows in their lungs, and had never tested for antibodies. The couple took 10 daily vitamins and high-protein supplements, and the younger wife finally developed antibodies, but colleagues have not yet.

"It's a little bit weird, " Li Yan said. "Some people don't have antibodies, but they get sick, and some people don't have antibodies, but they don't have any clinical symptoms. " And I'm not letting him out of here.

Zhang Xiaochun's colleague's experience is more twists and turns. The colleague, who is in his 30s, contracted a new coronavirus two months ago and was hospitalized for a week or so, with no inflammation in his lungs, two negative nucleic acid tests, and no clinical symptoms.

20 days after discharge, the nucleic acid test was positive, was sent to the isolation point isolation, during the period of no clinical symptoms, a few days after the review, turned negative. When the 14-day quarantine period came to an end, the test came back positive, "leaving everyone depressed and not knowing what to do. He had to stay in the quarantine until the nucleic acid continued to be negative or antibodies were detected. "

Zhang Xiaochun said that patients who do not produce antibodies or produce antibodies relatively late, after discharge, once the immunity is reduced, can not resist the virus, easy to repeat the disease, the amount of virus in the body increased, at this time, and then do nucleic acid reexamination, is likely to Fuyang.

Zhang Xiaochun stressed that repeated illness can not be counted as a "relapse" , but "the same virus repeated, may also be infectious. ".

In order to avoid the patient's condition repeatedly to infect the human, the sixth edition and the seventh edition diagnosis and treatment plan, all proposed the discharge patient isolation, and carries on the health surveillance.

Two researchers from Peking University and the Chinese Academy of Sciences published a paper in the National Science Review on March 3, saying that the new coronavirus has produced 149 mutations and evolved into two subtypes, which are very different from each other. At the same time, CSIRO said the new coronavirus was mutating, the The Hindu reported. Brazilian researchers also found two confirmed cases in the country, one similar to the virus found in Germany and one similar to the virus found in the UK.

At present, there is no definite conclusion about whether the new coronavirus mutates in China. "clinically, it doesn't look like the virus has mutated, " Liu youning, a 301 Military Hospital expert and head of the army's forward expert team, told CCTV

Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou Worries that studies now show that there are two types of coronaviruses, and that patients who leave the hospital may get infected again if their antibodies fail to resist another variant.

In addition, whether the new coronavirus will develop into a chronic carrier virus, is also of concern.

In an interview with News 1 + 1 on February 19, academician Wang Chen said that the SARS virus was highly contagious and pathogenic, and could not survive and continue to spread because if it killed its host, it would no longer be there. The possibility that the new coronavirus could become chronic, as long-term as the flu, "is a real possibility, and we need to be prepared for that. "

Zhang shares the view that the new coronavirus could develop into a chronic carrier, like the flu, that co-exists with humans for a long time. As a result, the virus becomes more and more infectious, less pathogenic, and the patient has mild or no symptoms.

However, Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou believes that the new coronavirus is not likely to be chronic carriers, but there may be a small amount of the virus attached to the patient's Nasopharyngeal, Oropharyngeal Mucosa, generally do not attack, and does not affect the respiratory tract Mucosa.

Another expert, who asked not to be named, said there was no need to panic too much about the possibility of chronic transmission of the new coronavirus. In the case of Hepatitis B, about 90 percent of the country's 120 million hepatitis B carriers do not get sick.

Peng Zhiyong felt that the lower the virulence of the virus, the higher the risk of developing chronic diseases. "whether the new coronavirus will become a chronic carrier is still too early and remains to be seen, " he said

Focus on "Fu Yang" infectivity

"Fu Yang" patients with infectious, but also the focus of public opinion.

Li Yueping, director of the ICU of the Infectious Disease Center of the Eighth People's Hospital of Guangzhou, said at a news conference held by the Guangzhou municipal government on February 25 that it was technically difficult to distinguish between live and dead viruses in patients with Fuyang. But all of their close contacts were negative. This shows that Fu Yang patients did not appear infectious phenomenon.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Director of ICU, infection center, Guangzhou Eighth People's Hospital, Li Yueping. Liang Weipeitu, NANDU reporter

In response to the patient's condition, Xu Haibo, director of the imaging department at Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, and his team studied four infected patients and found that they tested positive for nucleic acid five to 13 days after their discharge from the hospital; within four to five days, three nucleic acid tests, all positive; switch to another manufacturer's Kit, all positive. During isolation, 4 people had no symptoms, lungs the same as when they left the hospital, no exposure to people with respiratory symptoms. Three of them were discharged from the hospital and put under isolation at home. Their families were not infected. As a result, he said, "a certain percentage of people who are cured may still be carriers of the virus. " The study was published Feb. 27 in the Journal of the American Medical Association, a Leading Medical Journal.

Xu told The Paper that the mechanism of the disease was not clear, and that it needed to be studied to determine whether patients with the disease were contagious. The first step was to rule out "false negative" conditions caused by inadequate or heterogeneous testing.

Most of the patients Peng encountered had no clinical symptoms. "their infectivity needs to be observed again, and it may be some time before a full conclusion can be drawn, " he said. "It also needs time to verify what will happen after the patient recovers his Yang. "

Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou suggested that patients should be well protected after discharge, wear masks, pay attention to hygiene habits, family members also do a good job of protection, to reduce the possibility of infection. He believes that Fuyang patients may remain in the body virus, but not much, less infectious, after discharge to designated places for 14 days of medical isolation, will further reduce the infectivity.

At present, the seventh version of the diagnosis and treatment program, patients are advised to discharge the second week, the fourth week of follow-up. Emperor Taizu of Later Zhou recommends stratified follow up after discharge, with national guidelines for young people who have recovered well, and follow up after the first week of discharge for patients who have used steroids, are critically ill, or are elderly, to identify patients with recurrent or recurrent disease earlier.
